rm(list=ls())
df <- read.csv("StuAddr_SP2019.csv")
dim(df)
## [1] 38758     4
colnames(df)
## [1] "STREET1"     "STREET2"     "STREET3"     "CITY_ST_ZIP"
library(plyr)
str3 <- count(df$STREET3)
str3 <- str3[order(str3$freq, decreasing = TRUE),c(1,2)]
freq <- as.integer(as.matrix(str3$freq)[-1, ]) #drop the 30324 missing values
barplot(freq)

library(tidyr)
data <- separate(df, CITY_ST_ZIP, into=c("county","state","zip"), sep=" ")
library(dplyr)
##

data <- mutate(data, address = paste (STREET3, county, state))
#View(data)

Geocode Data

library(ggmap)

for (i in 1:nrow(data)){
  result <- geocode(data$address[i], output = "latlona", source = "google")
  data$longitude[i] <- as.numeric(result[1])
  data$latitude[i] <- as.numeric(result[2])
  data$geoAddress[i] <- as.character(result[3])
}

# write.csv(data, "geocoded.csv")

Geomap

geodata <- read.csv("geocoded.csv")

#pdf("map.pdf") 

library(ggmap)
## Warning: package 'ggmap' was built under R version 3.5.3
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Google's Terms of Service: https://cloud.google.com/maps-platform/terms/.
## Please cite ggmap if you use it! See citation("ggmap") for details.
map <- get_map(location="UIUC, IL", zoom = 15, scale = 2)
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=UIUC,%20IL&zoom=15&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=terrain&language=en-EN&key=xxx
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=UIUC,+IL&key=xxx
map <- ggmap(map) + geom_point(aes(longitude, latitude), 
                        fill= "red", shape = 21,
                        data=geodata)
map 

#dev.off()

Heatmap

tb <- table(geodata$geoAddress)
addr_fac <- factor(geodata$geoAddress, 
                   levels = names(tb[order(tb, decreasing = TRUE)]))


heatmap <- map + 
           stat_bin2d(data=geodata, 
                      aes(x=longitude, y=latitude, color=addr_fac, 
                          fill=addr_fac),
                      size=0.5, alpha=0.5, bins = 30) 

heatmap
